# =============================================================================
# FERPA GATE — canvas-toolbox grader pipeline
#
# ★ DO NOT REMOVE OR LOOSEN ENTRIES IN THIS FILE WITHOUT REVIEW ★
#
# This .gitignore is the SINGLE place that ensures student-identifying
# artifacts never reach git. Every entry below is here because losing it
# would create a FERPA-reportable incident.
#
# The student files in `submissions_raw/` carry names in their filenames
# AND inside their bodies. Even AFTER de-identification, the original files
# stay local. The .keymap.json and .known_names.txt and .fetch_log.json
# files are the bridge back to real students; if they leak, the whole
# anonymization story collapses retroactively.
#
# Patterns are matched at ANY nesting depth (leading `**/`) so creating a
# sub-cohort folder like `grading/spring2026/kc1/submissions_raw/` is also
# caught.
# =============================================================================

# What the consumer repo SHOULD commit from grading/ (the instructor's own
# work, no student data):
#   - RUBRIC.md, OUTCOMES.md, config.json per assignment
#   - PROCESS.md per assignment (operational doc)
#   - template/ directory (assignment-template source files)
#   - answer_keys/README.md (the convention; not the keys themselves)
#   - grading_readme.md / GRADING_PROCESS.md at the grading/ root

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Submission files — names live in filenames AND bodies. NEVER COMMIT.
# Matched at any depth so sub-cohort folders are caught too.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
submissions_raw/
**/submissions_raw/
**/_raw/

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# De-identified mirrors — keyed and safe in principle, but kept local as
# defense in depth (a de-id bug shouldn't be the first line of defense).
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
submissions_deid/
**/submissions_deid/
**/_deid/

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# FERPA bridge files — these map opaque keys back to real students. If
# committed, the whole anonymization story unwinds retroactively. NEVER COMMIT.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
.keymap.json
**/.keymap.json
.fetch_log.json
**/.fetch_log.json
.known_names.txt
**/.known_names.txt

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Push gate + audit trail — has user_ids and scores; instructor-only.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
.mark_reviewed
**/.mark_reviewed
.push_log.md
**/.push_log.md

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Re-identified review sheet — has user_ids and scores; instructor-only.
# Glob form covers the multi-output dual-push case (e.g. .review_your_grade.csv).
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
.review.csv
.review*.csv
**/.review.csv
**/.review*.csv

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Per-student feedback + consensus artifacts — instructor-only until push.
# Comments may quote student work; safer kept local. (A course that wants
# to commit pseudonymized feedback can override per-folder.)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
feedback/
**/feedback/

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Answer keys — instructor's own work, but contain hardcoded tokens/PATs and
# the reference solution. ALWAYS local. README + .gitkeep allowed.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
answer_keys/*/
!answer_keys/README.md
!answer_keys/.gitkeep

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Python bytecode
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
__pycache__/
*.pyc
